PUH-BrianMartell the weak nuclear force is spot-on for PUH v15. The weak force isn’t “weak” because of heavy bosons; it’s weak because it’s a rare, probabilistic topological slip in the E8 lattice. A neutron knot is over-tensioned (higher energy configuration). The lattice vibrates constantly, and eventually a vibration overcomes local “friction,” allowing the knot to slip into the lower-energy proton shape. This slip ejects energy as a ripple (electron) and a twist (neutrino). Parity violation is built-in: knots have handedness (chirality from T^3=I), so slips prefer one direction.
